column5: will be at nungesser lake labor day week-----never been there---any info would be appreciated......
what camp on Nungesser are you staying at? I have stayed at Birchpoint a couple of times. Tim
Take some preserved minnows and gulp curly tail grubs. Great lake, lots of structure
the camp is owned by the people at Goose Bay Camp on lac seul---don't know if it has a name----

Been to Goose Bay numerous times and also to one of the other camps on the lake. Haven't been to Goose Bay for 10+ years though. Have fun dodging the rocks on the river during the portage into the lake. Some of the best fishing is right around Goose Bay Camp.

Was at the goose bay outpost earlier this month. Fishing was good, not great. Walleyes in 18-21 ft. You should get a lake map, marked with places to fish. Used live bait and plastic. Nice lake. Would enjoy hearing how your week goes.
How was your trip? We have been going to this lake for about 10 years and staying at NLL. Love the lake, lots of walleye and big pike.
Is kevin geary's place still open?
Do you mean for the year or at all? He was there operating in June of this year when we were at the lake. Saw lots of his boats out and around.
